props.custom_script:
<script type="application/javascript">
const logo =
"https://u.vrgmetri.com/gb-sms-prod-1/media/2021-3/bzcjqd/b9bb0cc0-6ffa-4cda-9b99-ed080d7ff8b4/o/Banner-w-Patent-Pending3.png";

/*"https://u.vrgmetri.com/gb-sms-prod-1/media/2021-1/maxjnd/d37912d6-8559-42c7-b9d1-0bb02d27de9b/o/Notch1.png";*/

// change mask image below
const maskImage = "https://u.vrgmetri.com/gb-sms-prod-1/media/2021-3/bzcjqd/76502903-a864-4b65-9192-43df3b03e4b3/o/MetroFordAnimatedText1.gif";


function createHeader() {
  const header = document.createElement("div");
  header.id = "ford_header";
  header.style["z-index"] = 1;
  header.style.position = "fixed";
  header.style.top = "0";
  header.style.left = "calc(50% - 10vw)";

  document.getElementById("app").appendChild(header);

  const img = document.createElement("img");
  img.id = "ford_img";
  img.style.width = "17vw";
  img.style.height = "auto";
  img.style["max-width"] = "600px";
  img.style["min-width"] = "130px";
  img.style.visibility = "hidden";
  img.src = logo;
  header.appendChild(img);
}

function fixPosition() {
  console.log("fixing positions");
  const fordImg = document.getElementById("ford_img");
  const fordHeader = document.getElementById("ford_header");
  const offset = fordImg.width / 2;
  fordHeader.style.left = "calc(50% - " + offset + "px)";
  fordImg.style.visibility = 'visible';
}

function createMask() {
  const mask = document.createElement("div");
  mask.id = "mask";
  mask.style.position = "fixed";
  mask.style.top = 0;
  mask.style.right = 0;
  mask.style.bottom = 0;
  mask.style.left = 0;
  mask.style.background = "#000";

  mask.style.display = "flex";
  mask.style["justify-content"] = "center";
  mask.style["align-items"] = "center";

  document.getElementById("app").appendChild(mask);

  const img = document.createElement("img");
  img.id = "mask_img";

// change dimensions below
  img.style.width = "600px";
  img.style.height = "auto";
  img.src = maskImage;
  mask.appendChild(img);

// adding a timeout here to remove mask after few seconds
// timeout is in miliseconds. 10 secs = 10000 miliseconds
  setTimeout(function() {
    document.getElementById("app").removeChild(mask);
  } , 10000);
}

function isIOS() {
  return /(iPad|iPhone|iPod)/g.test(navigator.userAgent);
}

createHeader();

// adding a condition to not show the mask on ios
if(!isIOS()) {
  createMask();
}
fixPosition();

window.addEventListener("orientationchange", function () {
  const fordImg = document.getElementById("ford_img");
  fordImg.style.visibility = 'hidden';
  fixPosition();
});

</script>

props.ssml:
Headlamps.
Daytime Running Lamps.
Halogen Headlamps.
Autolamp (On or Off).

AUTOMATIC HIGH-BEAMS.
We’ve all been there. Heading into a pitch-black stretch of road and having to turn on the high beams, then forgetting to turn them off as oncoming traffic approaches. Now, unlit roads, dark peripheries and other low-visibility situations don’t have to catch you off guard. Auto High-Beam Headlamps can sense poor lighting conditions and switch on to light your path ahead. They even sense oncoming headlights and dim automatically so you don’t have to worry about blinding other drivers. So you can keep your focus - and both hands on the wheel.

props.ssml:
2.7 Litre ECOBOOST® V6.
Engineer it with the Ford port-fuel and direct-injection (PFDI) system with two injectors per cylinder, dual overhead cam design with variable intake or exhaust cam timing, plus twin intercooled turbochargers for on-demand power. And the available 2.7 Litre EcoBoost® V6 with 10-speed transmission is strong. Its upper block and cylinders are made of the same high-strength compacted graphite iron used in the Super Duty® 6.7 Litre Power Stroke®Turbo Diesel.

props.ssml: Pre-Collision Assist with Automatic Emergency Braking is designed to scan the road ahead and can alert you to a potential collision with a vehicle or pedestrian detected ahead of you. If an impact becomes imminent and you don’t take corrective action, the brakes can apply automatically. But they’ll only activate if they’re needed.
A two-bar-style black grille with black surround and black accents is standard on the F-one fifty XL.

FULLY BOXED STEEL FRAME.
F-one fifty has toughness in its bones, built with a fully boxed frame made of high-strength steel and large cross sections. And while it's undoubtedly strong and rigid, this frame is also relatively lightweight because many of the components are fabricated using a state-of-the-art roll-forming process.

Retractable Tonneau pickup box cover.
F-one fifty lends a hand wherever it can. While you’re packing up, your truck can help you save time covering and uncovering your pickup box with an available retractable tonneau pickup box cover.

props.ssml:
Tailgate Step with Tailgate Work Surface.
The tailgate step makes it easier to get into and out of the pickup bed. The tailgate includes a new integrated work surface that proves indispensable at your campsite or worksite.

BEST-IN-CLASS AVAILABLE TOWING.
The all-new 2021 F-one fifty doesn’t pull punches, But it does pull just about everything else with best-in-class 14,000 lbs of available towing capacity.

Rear View Camera gives you a sharp view without having to crane your head 180 degrees to look back. Just make sure to keep the camera lens free of debris (like snow or dust) so you can navigate reverse with more confidence. It also includes a dynamic hitch assist feature that provides a sight line to help you direct your hitch ball to your trailer tongue.

props.ssml:
Pro Power Onboard - 2kW.
This 2kW power output turns your F-one fifty into a generator. Available with optional gas engines.

400Watt Outlet.
This 400Watt power outlet, available with gas and diesel engines, is located in the bed (not available with 8-feet box) and gives you a convenient place to plug in small equipment.

BoxLink™.
Flexible, configurable universal pickup box interface system secures a wide variety of available Ford and aftermarket accessories such as ramps, storage bins, dividers and many others.

BEST-IN-CLASS AVAILABLE PAYLOAD.
Reducing weight is an effective way to increase payload. That’s just another huge benefit of the redesigned F-one fifty body and bed built of lightweight, high-strength, military-grade aluminum alloy. What results is a best-in-class available payload rating of 3,325 lbs, in F-one fifty models powered by the legendary available Ford 5 point zero Litre V8.

props.ssml:
Class IV Trailer Hitch.
Optional on XL and XLT Standard. Included on XLT Mid and High. Standard on LARIAT, King Ranch,® Platinum and Limited.
Package includes:
• 4-pin or 7-pin wiring harness.
• Class IV trailer hitch receiver.
• Smart Trailer Tow Connector (includes BLIS® with Trailer Tow Coverage where BLIS is available).

POWER TAILGATE.
Save yourself a trip. Not only does a Ford F-one fifty give you plenty of room to pack your tools, the power up and down tailgate also makes for easy loading and unloading. The available power tailgate lets you automatically lift and lower your tailgate from a distance with your key fob or with the in-vehicle button.

props.ssml:
REAR LOCKING UNDER-SEAT STORAGE.
When you need things under lock and key, the available folding, lockable under-seat storage is the spot. It’s integrated with the floor and perfect for storing loose items or anything you want to keep concealed and secure. The rear flat load floor also makes it easy to load and haul large items in the cab.

props.ssml:
Gauges and Meters.
Fuel.
Oil Pressure.
Transmission Temperature.
Engine Coolant Temperature.
Speedometer.
Odometer.
Tachometer.

The Lane-Keeping System can help you stay in your lane, even during a moment of distraction. This smart feature scans your vehicle’s position between the lines in the road ahead and can alert you if you’re starting to edge out of your lane. Having trouble staying on track? After you’ve drifted a few times, you’ll see a coffee cup icon, letting you know it’s time to take a break.

360-Degree Camera Package.
With the available 360-Degree Camera Package on your F-one fifty, you have a bird’s-eye view all around your truck. This feature uses four cameras — one in the grille, one on the tailgate and one under each sideview mirror — to stitch together four images to create a 360-degree view. And now you can keep tabs on your cargo with a new bed-view camera.

Dual-Zone Electronic Automatic Temperature Control.
This available feature provides individual climate settings for you and your front-seat passenger.

8 INCH CENTER STACK SCREEN.
The standard 8-inch touchscreen helps keep you connected on the road and brings an additional element of productivity to your interior. And with SYNC® 4 included, everything you need is at your command.

props.embed_string: <iframe src="https://video-app-4056-9370-dev.twil.io/?passcode=66687240569370&roomName=auto" style="width:100%; height:100%" allow="camera;microphone;"/>

props.ssml:
Interior Work Surface.
Sometimes getting your hands dirty means dusting off your keyboard. When it’s time to take care of business, there’s no place better to work than an F-one fifty. It’s equipped to enhance your productivity, with a shifter that stows so the available Interior Work Surface can fold directly from the center console or pivot out with bench seats. And when your truck is your office, you know it’s going to be a short commute.

With FordPass™ Connect, Ford owners and passengers can enjoy an available 4G LTE in-vehicle Wi-Fi hotspot, powered by AT&T. Up to 10 devices can connect at once, and you can use FordPass to keep track of your Wi-Fi data usage. You can access the hotspot up to 50 feet outside the vehicle. Now you can stay connected, even as you roam the highways.

MAX RECLINE SEATS.
Loading bricks, Chopping wood, Baling hay, And after all the hard work? New available Max Recline Seats fold almost completely flat to help you take a well-deserved break.
